amps or processing logs to confirm the order.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"The test requires real files with real filesystem timestamps and real watcher arrival to catch the failure; pure logic tests with injected timestamps would not verify actual filesystem timestamp behavior.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"A file still being written is not picked up for processing until writing is complete","minimum_level":"System","justification":"The real failure is that the daemon processes a file before all bytes are written. This requires detection of file-write completion, which is OS-dependent (file locking, size changes, handle state). The daemon must either check file size/lock status or wait for the watcher to stabilize. The only reliable way to test this is with real open file handles and OS-level filesystem state. Mocking a partial file or file state would not catch failures in detecting when writing has actually ceased.","test_description":"Open a file for writing without closing it, trigger the watcher (or wait for auto-detection), verify the daemon does not process the incomplete file. Then close the file handle, verify the daemon picks up the now-complete file and processes it. May require checking file size, inode changes, or lock status.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"The test requires real open file handles and OS filesystem state; mocking file state would not verify the daemon's actual in-progress file detection.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.8,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13529,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13529},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"